This is a quick fix for a problem we've been seeing in our build host. I guess we should probably add a way for the user to specify the encoding in the target specification. Personally I think using the existing "format" concept is a better fit for setting text mode/encoding than using open flags similarly to the python file `open`. Would be nice if open() pretty much only set if a file is opened for reading or writing and the rest of all format specification is done on the target level of the abstraction. This was at least part of the vision for the Target abstraction when we came up with it, that you wouldn't need to know a whole lot about how the content was stored when you consume a target in a subsequent task.

